    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-05-15T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-05-15T09:00:00-05:00" n="89"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d89">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">340.1115A/617a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="46" xml:id="d89fn46">Sent on the same date to the Consul
                        General at Genoa (No. 120), the Ambassador in Italy (No. 118), and the
                        Ministers in Yugoslavia (No. 28) and Hungary (No. 97).</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-05-15T10:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 15, 1940—10 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>47. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>, United States Lines, now at Genoa
                    planning sail Saturday. Ship has sold many passages but has some additional
                    space and has 800 cots. Consular certificate being issued and ship prepared to
                    accommodate passengers aboard ship until boat sails. This information is sent
                    you for the benefit of Americans in your district desiring repatriation and who
                    may desire to avail themselves of the sailing of the <hi rend="italic"
                        >Washington.</hi>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
